verbose_text: The total or accumulative forward displacement of a microbubble during the entire 10-sec ultrasound application period appeared to be positively correlated with the overall cytoskeleton contractile force increase during the 30-min observation period (XREF_FIG) (R 2 = 0.72 and n = 13), suggesting the important role of the physical displacement of integrin mediated cell adhesion in regulating cytoskeleton contractile force response.
